This bash script will rename an entire directory of DV files (packaged from MOV files via DV Rescue) after the timestamps embedded within the file:. Note that it requires mediainfo

Here's the script: "

for file in $(find . -name \*.mov | sed -e 's/ /@@@/g')
do
file=$(echo "$file" | sed -e 's/@@@/ /g')
record_date=$(mediainfo --Inform=General "$file" | grep 'Recorded date')

if [[ -n "$record_date" ]]; then
    date=$(echo "$record_date" | cut -c44-59 | tr ' ' '-' | tr ':' '-')
    new_name="$(echo $(dirname "$file")/"$date".mov)"
    echo "Found recording date -> renaming $file to $new_name"
    mv "$file" "$new_name"
else
    echo "No recording date found in file $file -- skipping"
fi
done

"

----------------------
And to run this script, execute using the following commands:

step 1) cd ~/Documents/Scripts/
step 2) chmod +x your_script.sh 
step 3) ./your_script.sh

or 


step 4) bash your_script.sh 
